name: David Letterman
monologue: I don't know what they are protesting at Occupy Wall Street but I'm on their side. But 10,000 protestors and one Porta Potty?

name: David Letterman
monologue: Top Ten Things Gadhafi Wants To Say From Hell

name: Conan O'Brian
monologue: McDonald’s just announced that they will sell the McRib sandwich only until Nov. 14. So unfortunately, it looks like I'll have to cook for Thanksgiving after all.

name: Conan O'Brian
monologue: The New York Times reports that Moammar Gadhafi spent his last days hovering between defiance and delusion, surviving on rice and pasta. In other words, Gadhafi spent his last days as a sophomore in college. That's what I did.

name: Conan O'Brian
monologue: A bank in Washington was robbed by two men in George W. Bush masks. Luckily, right afterwards two guys in President Obama masks came and bailed the bank out, so everything is fine.

name: Conan O'Brian
monologue: President Obama was back in Los Angeles today, where he will appear on the "Tonight Show" with Jay Leno, to highlight the one job that was saved during his administration.

name: Jay Leno
monologue: A judge has ordered Lindsay Lohan to work at the L.A. morgue. This way she can do community service and visit her career at the same time.

name: Jay Leno
monologue: It seemed that after he was killed, Gadhafi's body was stored at a commercial freezer at a shopping mall. It's one thing to hunt a guy down and shoot him twice in the head, but then to drag him to the mall? Come on, guys hate that.

name: Jay Leno
monologue: The guy who killed Gadhafi was wearing a New York Yankees cap at the time. So, for at least one Yankees fan, it turned out to be a pretty good October.

name: Jay Leno
monologue: I'm very excited that President Obama is coming tomorrow night and as you know he's on his nationwide “I Whacked Another Terrorist” tour.

name: Jimmy Fallon
monologue: Yesterday on CNN, Joe Biden said he hasn’t made up his mind about whether he’ll run for president in 2016. Which raises the question: “Who was raising that question?”

name: Jimmy Fallon
monologue: The iPod’s been around for 10 years, which is also the length of time it takes to untangle your iPod headphones.

name: Jimmy Fallon
monologue: Wal-Mart is planning to reduce its healthcare plan for new employees. Which explains why today, my greeter was like, “Hello, welcome to Wal-Mart. Would you mind checking out this mole?”

name: Jimmy Fallon
monologue: I just read that a bear broke into a candy store in Tennessee and started eating all the candy. That’s right, a live bear filled with candy. Or as Sarah Palin calls that, “the best piñata ever.”

name: Jimmy Kimmel
monologue: I personally didn't watch "Dancing With the Stars" tonight because if there's anything I learned from the new "Footloose" remake, it’s that dancing is a sin and should not be tolerated.

name: Jimmy Kimmel
monologue: The world was supposed to end Friday. I don't think it did, though. Harold Camping also predicted the apocalypse was going to happen back in May and I don't think that one happened either. Well, you know what they say, the third apocalypse is the charm.

name: Jimmy Kimmel
monologue: This is reported to be the 12th time Camping has predicted the end of the world, the first time being in 1978. Not only is he bad at predicting things but he's kind of a bummer to hang out with.

name: Jimmy Kimmel
monologue: Halloween is one week away. If you're going to a party, you’d better figure out a costume or you'll be stuck wearing a salad bowl on your head and calling yourself Justin Bieber.
